Burton first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2020 U.S. census]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=2020 Geography Changes|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/acs/technical-documentation/table-and-geography-changes/2020/geography-changes.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=}}</ref>

As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/profile?g=1600000US1710006 |access-date=2022-06-28 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> there were 103 people, 27 households, and 13 families residing in the CDP. The population density was {{Convert|312.12|PD/sqmi|PD/km2}}. There were 44 housing units at an average density of {{Convert|133.33|/sqmi|/km2}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 98.06% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.97% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], and 0.97% from two or more races.

